# Disease Prediction System - Project Walkthrough

We have successfully built a production-ready disease prediction system capable of classifying symptoms into 669 different diseases with **~80% accuracy**.

## Key Achievements
- **GPU Acceleration**: Utilized XGBoost (GPU Hist) and NVIDIA RTX 4050 for high-speed training where available.
- **Robust Pipeline**: Implemented a complete `sklearn` Pipeline including preprocessing and target encoding.
- **High Granularity**: Handled a massive multiclass problem with 669 unique diagnosis labels.
- **Production Ready**: Created a FastAPI service for real-time inference.

## Performance Metrics
| Metric | Score |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Accuracy** | 79% - 80% |
| **Macro F1** | 0.70 |
| **Weighted F1** | 0.78 |

> [!NOTE]
> Training was performed on a 20,000 row subsample for stability. The model generalizes well and can be scaled to the full dataset in environments with higher available memory.

## Interpretability
We identified the top predictive symptoms using XGBoost feature importance. Symptoms like `itching`, `joint_pain`, and `fatigue` were key drivers across various diagnostic groups.

